Mailchimp Open Commerce API API Reference

Welcome to the sample Mailchimp Open Commerce API reference. This is a live example of how you can use DociQL in conjunction with GraphQL to generate beautiful static documentation for your own APIs.

GraphQL is a query language for APIs and a runtime for fulfilling those queries with your existing data. GraphQL provides a complete and understandable description of the data in your API, gives clients the power to ask for exactly what they need and nothing more, makes it easier to evolve APIs over time, and enables powerful developer tools.

API Endpoints
Demandcluster Dev Server:
https://api.demandcluster.com/graphql
Contact: ron@demandcluster.com
Version: 1.0.0

Query Catalog

Base query to get product catalog information.

Query Catalog

Query Catalog

Fetch a list of products from a catalog.

shopIds:
string[]

Provide a list of shop IDs from which you want to get catalog items

tagIds:
string[]

Optionally provide a list of tag IDs to further filter the item list

booleanFilters:
CatalogBooleanFilter

Additional filters to apply

searchQuery:
string

Optional text search query

after:
object

Return only results that come after this cursor. Use this with first to specify the number of results to return.

before:
object

Return only results that come before this cursor. Use this with last to specify the number of results to return.

first:
object

Return at most this many results. This parameter may be used with either after or offset parameters.

last:
object

Return at most this many results. This parameter may be used with the before parameter.

offset:
integer

Return only results that come after the Nth result. This parameter may be used with the first parameter.

sortOrder:
SortOrder

Return results sorted in this order

sortByPriceCurrencyCode:
string

Provide a Currency code if sortBy is minPrice

sortBy:
CatalogItemSortByField

By default, items are sorted by when they were last updated, most recently updated first. Set this to sort by one of the other allowed fields

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
query catalogItems($shopIds: [ID]!, $tagIds: [ID], $booleanFilters: [CatalogBooleanFilter], $searchQuery: String, $after: ConnectionCursor, $before: ConnectionCursor, $first: ConnectionLimitInt, $last: ConnectionLimitInt, $offset: Int, $sortOrder: SortOrder, $sortByPriceCurrencyCode: String, $sortBy: CatalogItemSortByField){
  catalogItems(shopIds: $shopIds, tagIds: $tagIds, booleanFilters: $booleanFilters, searchQuery: $searchQuery, after: $after, before: $before, first: $first, last: $last, offset: $offset, sortOrder: $sortOrder, sortByPriceCurrencyCode: $sortByPriceCurrencyCode, sortBy: $sortBy){
  }
}
Variables
{
  "shopIds": [
    "string"
  ],
  "tagIds": [
    "string"
  ],
  "booleanFilters": [
    {
      "name": "string",
      "value": "boolean"
    }
  ],
  "searchQuery": "string",
  "offset": "integer",
  "sortOrder": "string",
  "sortByPriceCurrencyCode": "string",
  "sortBy": "string"
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
CatalogItemConnection
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "catalogItems": {}
  }
}
Query Catalog

Query Product

Fetch a single product from a catalog.

shopId:
string

ID of the shop that owns the catalog product. Not required but highly recommended if you have multiple shops and slugOrId is a slug because slugs are unique only within a shop.

slugOrId:
string

Provide either a product ID or slug

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
query catalogItemProduct($shopId: ID, $slugOrId: String){
  catalogItemProduct(shopId: $shopId, slugOrId: $slugOrId){
    _id
    createdAt
    updatedAt
  }
}
Variables
{
  "shopId": "string",
  "slugOrId": "string"
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
CatalogItemProduct
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "catalogItemProduct": {
      "_id": "string"
    }
  }
}

Channel Manager

Base query to get channel information.

Channel Manager

Get Channels

input:
IDchannelsearch

Get channels input

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
query GetChannels($input: IDchannelsearch){
  GetChannels(input: $input){
  }
}
Variables
{
  "input": {
    "channelId": "number",
    "exportId": "number",
    "first": "object",
    "offset": "object",
    "search": "string",
    "shopId": "string"
  }
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
ResultChannelInfo
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "GetChannels": {}
  }
}

Schema Definitions

Account: object

Represents a single user account

_id:
ID

The account ID

addressBook:
AddressConnection

A list of physical or mailing addresses associated with this account

adminUIShops:
Shop

A list of shops this user can administer with the admin UI

bio:
String

Bio to display on profile

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this account was created

currency:
Currency

The preferred currency used by this account

emailRecords:
EmailRecord

A list of email records associated with this account

firstName:
String

The first name of the person this account represents, if known

language:
String

The preferred language used by this account

lastName:
String

The last name of the person this account represents, if known

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this account

name:
String

The full name of the person this account represents, if known

note:
String

Some note about this account

picture:
String

URL of picture to display on profile

preferences:
JSONObject

An object storing plugin-specific preferences for this account

primaryEmailAddress:
Email

The primary email address for the account. This matches the address in emailRecords where provides is default.

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this account was last updated

userId:
String

The Identity user ID with which this account is associated

username:
String

Username

groups:
GroupConnection

A paged list of the account groups in which this account is listed

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "addressBook": {
    "edges": [
      {
        "cursor": "object",
        "node": {
          "_id": "object",
          "address1": "string",
          "address2": "string",
          "city": "string",
          "company": "string",
          "country": "string",
          "firstName": "string",
          "fullName": "string",
          "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
          "isCommercial": "boolean",
          "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
          "lastName": "string",
          "metafields": [
            {
              "description": "string",
              "key": "string",
              "namespace": "string",
              "scope": "string",
              "value": "string",
              "valueType": "string"
            }
          ],
          "phone": "string",
          "postal": "string",
          "region": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "nodes": [
      {
        "_id": "object",
        "address1": "string",
        "address2": "string",
        "city": "string",
        "company": "string",
        "country": "string",
        "firstName": "string",
        "fullName": "string",
        "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
        "isCommercial": "boolean",
        "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
        "lastName": "string",
        "metafields": [
          {
            "description": "string",
            "key": "string",

            "value": "string",

AccountConnection: object

Wraps a list of Accounts, providing pagination cursors and information.

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

  • Relay Connection Documentation
  • Relay Connection Specification
  • Using Relay-style Connections With Apollo Client
edges:
AccountEdge

The list of nodes that match the query, wrapped in an edge to provide a cursor string for each

nodes:
Account

You can request the nodes directly to avoid the extra wrapping that NodeEdge has, if you know you will not need to paginate the results.

pageInfo:
PageInfo

Information to help a client request the next or previous page

totalCount:
Int

The total number of nodes that match your query

Example
{
  "edges": [
    {
      "cursor": "object",
      "node": {
        "_id": "object",
        "addressBook": {
          "edges": [

              "cursor": "object",

                "_id": "object",
                "address1": "string",
                "address2": "string",
                "city": "string",
                "company": "string",

                "firstName": "string",
                "fullName": "string",
                "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
                "isCommercial": "boolean",

                "metafields": [
                  {
                    "description": "string",
                    "key": "string",
                    "namespace": "string",
                    "scope": "string",
                    "value": "string",
                    "valueType": "string"
                  }
                ],
                "phone": "string",
                "postal": "string",
                "region": "string"
              }
            }
          ],
          "nodes": [
            {
              "_id": "object",
              "address1": "string",
              "address2": "string",
              "city": "string",
              "company": "string",
              "country": "string",

}

_id

object
createdAt

Date and time at which this account was created

object
updatedAt

Date and time at which this account was last updated

AddCartItemsPayload: object

The payload returned from the addCartItems mutation call

cart:
Cart

The modified cart. You should check incorrectPriceFailures and minOrderQuantityFailures for information necessary to display errors to the shopper. Some items may not have been added.

clientMutationId:
String

The same string you sent with the mutation params, for matching mutation calls with their responses

incorrectPriceFailures:
IncorrectPriceFailureDetails

Clients should check to see if any items failed to be added due to the price not matching the current price. In general, a user interface should display the correct current prices to the shopper, confirm that they still want to add the items, and then call createCart or addCartItems to do so.

Note that this field will always exist but may be an empty array if there were no failures of this type.

minOrderQuantityFailures:
MinOrderQuantityFailureDetails

Clients should check to see if any items failed to be added due to quantity being below the minimum order quantity defined for the product variant. In general, a user interface should display the minimum order quantity to the shopper and allow them to add that quantity or greater.

Note that this field will always exist but may be an empty array if there were no failures of this type.

Example

String

Country

String

fullName:
String

The full name of a person at this address

isBillingDefault:
Boolean

Is this the default address for billing purposes?

isCommercial:
Boolean

Is this a commercial address?

isShippingDefault:
Boolean

Is this the default address to use when selecting a shipping address at checkout?

String

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this address

phone:
String

A phone number for someone at this address

postal:
String

Postal code

region:
String

Cart: object

The cart holds selected items until order is placed.

_id:
ID

The Cart ID

account:
Account

The account that owns the cart. Some carts are created for anonymous users. Anonymous carts have a null account. Every account has exactly one cart per shop.

checkout:
Checkout

Holds all information collected for a cart during checkout

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which the cart was created, which is when the first item was added to it.

email:
String

An email address that has been associated with the cart

expiresAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which the cart will expire. Account carts usually do not expire, so they will have a null value here.

items:
CartItemConnection

The items that have been added to the cart. A cart is not created until the first item is added. Items can be removed from a cart, and a cart is not deleted if all items are removed from it. Because all items may have been removed, this may be an empty array.

missingItems:
CartItem

If any products or variants become hidden or are deleted after they were added to this cart, they'll be automatically moved from items to missingItems. Clients may want to use this to show an "items that are no longer available" list to storefront users.

If a product becomes visible again, the item will never be automatically moved from missingItems back to items, but clients may want to provide a way for users to manually do this.

referenceId:
String

If you integrate with third-party systems that require you to send the same ID for order calculations as for cart calculations, you may use this ID, which is the same on a cart as on the order placed from that cart. This ID can also be customized by plugins and is the best ID to use if it is necessary to show a cart ID in the user interface.

shop:
Shop

The shop that owns the cart.

totalItemQuantity:
Int

Total quantity of all items in the cart

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this cart was last updated.

surcharges:
AppliedSurcharge

Surcharges applied to this cart

taxSummary:
TaxSummary

A summary of calculated taxes for this cart. Null means "not able to calculate", such as when no fulfillment method has been selected for some fulfillment groups.

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "account": {
    "_id": "object",
    "addressBook": {
      "edges": [
        {
          "cursor": "object",
          "node": {
            "_id": "object",
            "address1": "string",
            "address2": "string",
            "city": "string",
            "company": "string",
            "country": "string",
            "firstName": "string",
            "fullName": "string",
            "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
            "isCommercial": "boolean",
            "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
            "lastName": "string",
            "metafields": [
              {
                "description": "string",
                "key": "string",
                "namespace": "string",
                "scope": "string",
                "value": "string",
                "valueType": "string"
              }
            ],
            "phone": "string",
            "postal": "string",
            "region": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "nodes": [
        {
          "_id": "object",
          "address1": "string",
          "address2": "string",

CartItem: object

A single item in a cart. The item contains information about an intended purchase.

_id:
ID

The cart item ID

addedAt:
DateTime

" The date and time at which this item was first added to the associated cart. If an item is added, removed, and then added again, this will reflect the most recent addition. However, if an item is added twice, the quantity will increase but this date will remain the initial added date.

attributes:
CartItemAttribute

FUTURE. Additional attributes of the chosen item. For example, if this item is for a product, socks, where blue and small options were chosen for some configurable attributes, then color:blue and size:small will be indicated here.

compareAtPrice:
Money

The current comparison (e.g., MSRP) price of the item

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which the cart item was created. If an item is added, removed, and then added again, the original item is destroyed and this field will reflect the time it was created for the most recent addition.

imageURLs:
ImageSizes

The URLs for a picture of the item in various sizes

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this cart item.

optionTitle:
String

The selected variant optionTitle

parcel:
ShippingParcel

Packing information such as item weight, height, length, and depth. Used for calculating shipping rates.

price:
Money

The current price of the item

priceWhenAdded:
Money

The price at which this item was listed when it was added to the cart

productConfiguration:
ProductConfiguration

The product and chosen options

productSlug:
String

The product's slug

productTags:
TagConnection

The list of tags that have been applied to this product

productType:
String

The type of product, used to display cart items differently

productVendor:
String

The product vendor

quantity:
Int

The quantity of this item that has been added to the cart. This must be a positive integer. Remove this CartItem from it's associated cart if you want 0 of this item.

shop:
Shop

The shop associated with this cart item.

subtotal:
Money

The current price of the item multiplied by the quantity

title:
String

A title for use in cart/orders that conveys the selected product's title + chosen options

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this item was last updated

variantTitle:
String

The selected variant title

inventoryAvailableToSell:
Int

The quantity of this item currently available to sell. This number is updated when an order is placed by the customer. This number does not include reserved inventory (i.e. inventory that has been ordered, but not yet processed by the operator). This is most likely the quantity to display in the storefront UI.

isBackorder:
Boolean

True if this item is currently sold out but allows backorders. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Backordered" indicator.

isLowQuantity:
Boolean

True if this item has a low available quantity (inventoryAvailableToSell) in stock. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Low Quantity" indicator.

isSoldOut:
Boolean

True if this item is currently sold out (inventoryAvailableToSell is 0). A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Sold Out" indicator when isBackorder is not also true.

isTaxable:
Boolean

Is this a taxable item?

tax:
Money

Total tax calculated for this item

taxCode:
String

The tax code for this item

taxableAmount:
Money

Amount of subtotal that is taxable

taxes:
CalculatedTax

List of calculated taxes due for this item

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "addedAt": "object",
  "attributes": [
    {
      "label": "string",
      "value": "string"
    }
  ],
  "compareAtPrice": {
    "amount": "number",
    "currency": {
      "_id": "object",
      "code": "string",
      "decimal": "string",
      "format": "string",
      "rate": "number",
      "scale": "number",
      "symbol": "string",
      "thousand": "string"
    },
    "displayAmount": "string"
  },
  "createdAt": "object",
  "imageURLs": {
    "large": "string",
    "medium": "string",
    "original": "string",
    "small": "string",
    "thumbnail": "string"
  },
  "metafields": [
    {
      "description": "string",
      "key": "string",
      "namespace": "string",
      "scope": "string",
      "value": "string",
      "valueType": "string"
    }
  ],
  "optionTitle": "string",
  "parcel": {
    "containers": "string",
    "distanceUnit": "string",
    "height": "number",

CartItemConnection: object

Wraps a list of CartItems, providing pagination cursors and information.

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

  • Relay Connection Documentation
  • Relay Connection Specification
  • Using Relay-style Connections With Apollo Client
edges:
CartItemEdge

The list of nodes that match the query, wrapped in an edge to provide a cursor string for each

nodes:
CartItem

You can request the nodes directly to avoid the extra wrapping that NodeEdge has, if you know you will not need to paginate the results.

pageInfo:
PageInfo

Information to help a client request the next or previous page

totalCount:
Int

The total number of nodes that match your query

{
  "edges": [
    {
      "cursor": "object",

Supported cart reconciliation modes

object

CartSummary: object

A summary of the totals for this cart

discountTotal:
Money

The total of all discounts applied, as a positive number

effectiveTaxRate:
Rate

The calculated tax-exclusive tax rate on all items and fulfillment prices (taxTotal / taxableAmount). This may be null, and there is a difference between null and 0. Null means not able to calculate, such as when no fulfillment method has been selected for some fulfillment groups.

fulfillmentTotal:
Money

The total price of all chosen fulfillment methods. This may be null, and there is a difference between null and 0. Null means not able to calculate, such as when no fulfillment method has been selected for some fulfillment groups.

itemTotal:
Money

The combined prices of all cart items

taxTotal:
Money

The total estimated tax that has not already been included in the item prices. This may be null, and there is a difference between null and 0. Null means not able to calculate, such as when no fulfillment methods have been selected or there is some other issue with the tax service.

taxableAmount:
Money

The total amount that was deemed taxable by the tax service

total:
Money

The sum of itemTotal, fulfillmentTotal, and taxTotal, minus discountTotal

surchargeTotal:
Money

The combined total of all surcharges. This may be null, and there is a difference between null and 0. Null means not able to calculate, such as when no fulfillment method has been selected for some fulfillment groups.

CatalogProduct: object

Represents a product that has been published into a shop catalog. The related Product is the source of truth for shop administrators, but that is then published to a catalog as a CatalogProduct, which is what should be displayed to shoppers who browse that catalog.

_id:
ID

The CatalogProduct ID. Do not assume that this is the same as the related product ID. See productId for that.

barcode:
String

The product barcode value, if it has one

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this CatalogProduct was created, which is when the related product was first published

description:
String

The full product description, which may have newline characters in it

height:
Float

The height of the product, if it has physical dimensions

isDeleted:
Boolean

True if this product has been deleted. Typically, deleted products are not returned in queries.

isVisible:
Boolean

True if this product should be shown to shoppers. Typically, non-visible products are not returned in queries.

length:
Float

The length of the product, if it has physical dimensions

media:
ImageInfo

All media for this product and its variants

metaDescription:
String

The product description to use for page description meta element in HTML

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this product

minOrderQuantity:
Int

The minimum quantity that must be added to a cart

originCountry:
String

The country of origin

pageTitle:
String

Subtitle

ShippingParcel

Dimensions and other information about the containers in which this product will be shipped

ImageInfo

The primary image

productId:
ID

The related Product ID

String

An arbitrary product type value, such as from an external system

shop:
Shop

The shop to which this product belongs

sku:
String

A stock keeping unit (SKU) identifier for this product

String

A URL-safe and human-readable string that uniquely identifies this product

socialMetadata:
SocialMetadata

Holds metadata specific to a specific social network service

supportedFulfillmentTypes:
FulfillmentType

When a shopper purchases this product, what types of fulfillment can they choose from?

title:
String

Product title

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this CatalogProduct was last updated, which is when the related product was most recently published

variants:
CatalogProductVariant

A flat list of all variants for this product

vendor:
String

The product vendor or manufacturer, for display

weight:
Float

The weight of the product on Earth, if it has physical dimensions

width:
Float

The width of the product, if it has physical dimensions

tagIds:
ID

The list of tag IDs that have been applied to this product

tags:
TagConnection

The list of tags that have been applied to this product

pricing:
ProductPricingInfo

Price and related information, per currency

isBackorder:
Boolean

True if every purchasable variant of this product is sold out but allows backorders. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Backordered" indicator.

isLowQuantity:
Boolean

True if at least one purchasable variant of this product has a low quantity in stock. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Low Quantity" indicator.

isSoldOut:
Boolean

True if every purchasable variant of this product is sold out. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Sold Out" indicator when isBackorder is not also true.

CatalogProductVariant: object

A variant of a catalog product

_id:
ID

The CatalogProductVariant ID. Do not assume that this is the same as the related variant ID. See variantId for that.

attributeLabel:
String

The attribute label describes the category of variant, for example, Color or Size. In most cases this will be the same for all variants at the same level.

barcode:
String

The product variant barcode value, if it has one

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this CatalogProductVariant was created, which is when the related product was first published

height:
Float

The height of the product variant, if it has physical dimensions

index:
Int

The position of this variant among other variants at the same level of the product-variant-option hierarchy

length:
Float

The length of the product, if it has physical dimensions

media:
ImageInfo

All media for this variant / option

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this product

minOrderQuantity:
Int

The minimum quantity that must be added to a cart

optionTitle:
String

A short title to use for product detail select lists

options:
CatalogProductVariant

Child variants, if any

originCountry:
String

The country of origin

primaryImage:
ImageInfo

The primary image of this variant / option

shop:
Shop

The shop to which this product variant belongs

sku:
String

A stock keeping unit (SKU) identifier for this product

title:
String

The full variant title for use on cart, checkout, and order summaries and on invoices. This fully describes the configured variant. For example, if this is an option with optionTitle Large, its parent variant has optionTitle Red, and the product title is Fancy T-Shirt, then this title will be something like Fancy T-Shirt - Red - Large.

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this CatalogProduct was last updated, which is when the related product was most recently published

variantId:
ID

The related Variant ID

weight:
Float

The weight of the product on Earth, if it has physical dimensions

width:
Float

The width of the product, if it has physical dimensions

pricing:
ProductPricingInfo

Price and related information, per currency

canBackorder:
Boolean

True for a purchasable variant if an order containing this variant will be accepted even when there is insufficient available inventory (inventoryAvailableToSell) to fulfill it immediately. For non-purchasable variants, this is true if at least one purchasable child variant can be backordered. A storefront UI may use this in combination with inventoryAvailableToSell to decide whether to show or enable an "Add to Cart" button.

inventoryAvailableToSell:
Int

The quantity of this item currently available to sell. This number is updated when an order is placed by the customer. This number does not include reserved inventory (i.e. inventory that has been ordered, but not yet processed by the operator). If this is a variant, this number is created by summing all child option inventory numbers. This is most likely the quantity to display in the storefront UI.

inventoryInStock:
Int

The quantity of this item currently in stock. This number is updated when an order is processed by the operator. This number includes all inventory, including reserved inventory (i.e. inventory that has been ordered, but not yet processed by the operator). If this is a variant, this number is created by summing all child option inventory numbers. This is most likely just used as a reference in the operator UI, and not displayed in the storefront UI.

isBackorder:
Boolean

True for a purchasable variant if it is sold out but allows backorders. For non-purchasable variants, this is true if every purchasable child variant is sold out but allows backorders. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Backordered" indicator.

isLowQuantity:
Boolean

True for a purchasable variant if it has a low available quantity (inventoryAvailableToSell) in stock. For non-purchasable variants, this is true if at least one purchasable child variant has a low available quantity in stock. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Low Quantity" indicator.

isSoldOut:
Boolean

True for a purchasable variant if it is sold out (inventoryAvailableToSell is 0). For non-purchasable variants, this is true if every purchasable child variant is sold out. A storefront UI may use this to decide to show a "Sold Out" indicator when isBackorder is not also true.

isTaxable:
Boolean

Is sales tax charged on this item?

taxCode:
String

An optional code which, if understood by the active tax service for the shop, determines how this product should be taxed

taxDescription:
String

A description to use for the tax line item on an invoice

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "attributeLabel": "string",
  "barcode": "string",
  "createdAt": "object",
  "height": "number",
  "index": "number",
  "length": "number",
  "media": [
    {
      "URLs": {
        "large": "string",
        "medium": "string",
        "original": "string",
        "small": "string",
        "thumbnail": "string"
      },
      "_id": "object",
      "priority": "number",
      "productId": "object",
      "variantId": "object"
    }

  "metafields": [
    {
      "description": "string",

    }

CreateCartPayload: object

The payload returned from the createCart mutation call

cart:
Cart

The created cart, if at least one item could be added. Otherwise null, and you should check incorrectPriceFailures and minOrderQuantityFailures for information necessary to display errors to the shopper.

clientMutationId:
String

The same string you sent with the mutation params, for matching mutation calls with their responses

incorrectPriceFailures:
IncorrectPriceFailureDetails

Clients should check to see if any items failed to be added due to the price not matching the current price. In general, a user interface should display the correct current prices to the shopper, confirm that they still want to add the items, and then call createCart or addCartItems to do so.

Note that this field will always exist but may be an empty array if there were no failures of this type.

minOrderQuantityFailures:
MinOrderQuantityFailureDetails

Clients should check to see if any items failed to be added due to quantity being below the minimum order quantity defined for the product variant. In general, a user interface should display the minimum order quantity to the shopper and allow them to add that quantity or greater.

Note that this field will always exist but may be an empty array if there were no failures of this type.

token:
String

If no identity token is provided with the request, then this mutation will create an anonymous cart. All anonymous carts have a token associated with them, which allows the client that created the cart to access that cart in the future. This is the only time this token is returned, so clients must store this securely in some type of local storage solution, and then send it along with all future anonymous cart queries and mutations.

Example
{
  "cart": {
    "_id": "object",
    "account": {
      "_id": "object",
      "addressBook": {
        "edges": [
          {
            "cursor": "object",
            "node": {
              "_id": "object",
              "address1": "string",
              "address2": "string",
              "city": "string",
              "company": "string",
              "country": "string",
              "firstName": "string",
              "fullName": "string",
              "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
              "isCommercial": "boolean",
              "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
              "lastName": "string",
              "metafields": [
                {
                  "description": "string",
                  "key": "string",
                  "namespace": "string",
                  "scope": "string",
                  "value": "string",
                  "valueType": "string"
                }
              ],
              "phone": "string",
              "postal": "string",
              "region": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "nodes": [
          {
            "_id": "object",
            "address1": "string",
            "address2": "string",
            "city": "string",
            "company": "string",
            "country": "string",
            "firstName": "string",
            "fullName": "string",
            "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
            "isCommercial": "boolean",
            "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
            "lastName": "string",
            "metafields": [
              {
                "description": "string",
                "key": "string",
                "namespace": "string"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }

CurrencyExchangeProductPricingInfo: object

The product price or price range for a specific currency

compareAtPrice:
Money

A comparison price value, usually MSRP. If price is null, this will also be null. That is, only purchasable variants will have a compareAtPrice.

currency:
Currency

The code for the currency these pricing details applies to

displayPrice:
String

UI should display this price. If a product has multiple potential prices depending on selected variants and options, then this is a price range string such as "$3.95 - $6.99". It includes the currency symbols.

maxPrice:
Float

The price of the most expensive possible variant+option combination

minPrice:
Float

The price of the least expensive possible variant+option combination

price:
Float

For variants with no options and for options, this will always be set to a price. For variants with options and products, this will be null. There must be a price for a variant to be added to a cart or purchased. Otherwise you would instead add one of its child options to a cart.

Example
{
  "compareAtPrice": {
    "amount": "number",
    "currency": {
      "_id": "object",
      "code": "string",
      "decimal": "string",
      "format": "string",
      "rate": "number",
      "scale": "number",
      "symbol": "string",
      "thousand": "string"
    },
    "displayAmount": "string"
  },
  "currency": {
    "_id": "object",
    "code": "string",
    "decimal": "string",

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

nodes:

DiscountConditions: object

Conditions for a discount code to be applied

Int

Account Limit

audience:
String

Audience that may apply this discount code

enabled:
Boolean

Is this discount code enabled

order:
DiscountConditionOrder

Order conditions

permissions:
String

Permissions that may apply this discount code

products:
String

Products that may apply this discount code

redemptionLimit:
Int

Number of times this code may be redeemed. Setting to 100 means the first 100 customers may apply this code. Setting this value to 0 will allow this code to be applied an infinite number of times.

tags:
String

Tags that may be apply this discount code

FlatRateFulfillmentRestriction: object

Defines a flat rate fulfillment method restriction.

_id:
ID

The restriction ID.

attributes:
AttributeRestrictions

Attribute restrictions. Multiple attribute restrictions are evaluated with AND. If both destination and attribute restrictions are present, they evaluate with AND.

destination:
DestinationRestrictions

Destination restrictions. If multiple destination restrictions are present, the most localized is the only one evaluated (i.e. evaluate postal if present, then region if present, then country). If both destination and attribute restrictions are present, they evaluate with AND.

methodIds:
ID

Method IDs to apply this restriction to. If none, applies to all methods as a universal restriction.

shopId:
ID

The shop ID

type:
RestrictionTypeEnum

The type of this restriction. Allowed types are allow or deny.

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "attributes": [
    {
      "operator": "string",
      "property": "string",
      "propertyType": "string",
      "value": "string"
    }
  ],
  "destination": {
    "country": [
      "string"
    ],
    "postal": [
      "string"
    ],
    "region": [
      "string"
    ]
  },
  "methodIds": [
    "object"
  ],
  "shopId": "object",
  "type": "string"
}

FulfillmentGroup: object

Links one or more cart items to fulfillment data. The most common example is having one FulfillmentGroup per shipping address.

_id:
ID

The fulfillment ID

availableFulfillmentOptions:
FulfillmentOption

The list of fulfillment options from which the shopper may choose. This list is created by taking the full list of registered fulfillment methods, keeping only those that match the fulfillment type of this group, and then calculating a price and handlingPrice for each based on the items in this group.

data:
FulfillmentData

Information needed by the fulfillment type to properly fulfill the order

items:
CartItem

The items that are included in this fulfillment group

selectedFulfillmentOption:
FulfillmentOption

The fulfillment method selected by a shopper for this group, with its associated price

shippingAddress:
Address

The shipping address collected for this group, if relevant

shop:
Shop

The shop that owns the items in this group and is responsible for fulfillment

type:
FulfillmentType

The fulfillment type. Any valid type that has been registered by a fulfillment plugin. Examples: shipping, digital

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "availableFulfillmentOptions": [
    {
      "fulfillmentMethod": {
        "_id": "object",
        "carrier": "string",
        "displayName": "string",
        "fulfillmentTypes": [
          "string"
        ],
        "group": "string",
        "name": "string"
      },
      "handlingPrice": {
        "amount": "number",
        "currency": {
          "_id": "object",
          "code": "string",
          "decimal": "string",
          "format": "string",
          "rate": "number",
          "scale": "number",
          "symbol": "string",
          "thousand": "string"
        },
        "displayAmount": "string"
      },
      "price": {
        "amount": "number",
        "currency": {
          "_id": "object",
          "code": "string",
          "decimal": "string",
          "format": "string",
          "rate": "number",
          "scale": "number",
          "symbol": "string",
          "thousand": "string"
        },

ID: object

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
object

Order: object

An order

_id:
ID

The Order ID

account:
Account

The account that placed the order. Some orders are created for anonymous users. Anonymous orders have a null account.

cartId:
ID

The ID of the cart that created this order. Carts are deleted after becoming orders, so this is just a reference.

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which the cart was created, which is when the first item was added to it.

displayStatus:
String

The order status for display in UI

email:
String

An email address that has been associated with the cart

fulfillmentGroups:
OrderFulfillmentGroup

One or more fulfillment groups. Each of these are fulfilled and charged as separate orders.

notes:
OrderNote

Notes about the order. This will always return an array but it may be empty

payments:
Payment

Payments that collectively have paid or will pay for the total amount due for this order. May be null if no payment is needed.

referenceId:
String

An ID by which the customer can reference this order when enquiring about it. A storefront user interface may show this to customers. Do not display other IDs (_id) to customers.

refunds:
Refund

Refunds that have been applied to the payments on this order.

shop:
Shop

The shop through which the order was placed

status:
String

The machine-readable order status.

summary:
OrderSummary

A summary of the totals for all fulfillment groups for this order

totalItemQuantity:
Int

Total quantity of all items in the order

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this order was last updated

surcharges:
AppliedSurcharge

Surcharges applied to this order

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "account": {
    "_id": "object",
    "addressBook": {
      "edges": [
        {
          "cursor": "object",
          "node": {
            "_id": "object",
            "address1": "string",
            "address2": "string",
            "city": "string",
            "company": "string",
            "country": "string",
            "firstName": "string",
            "fullName": "string",
            "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
            "isCommercial": "boolean",
            "isShippingDefault": "boolean",
            "lastName": "string",
            "metafields": [
              {
                "description": "string",
                "key": "string",
                "namespace": "string",
                "scope": "string",
                "value": "string",
                "valueType": "string"
              }
            ],
            "phone": "string",
            "postal": "string",
            "region": "string"
          }
        }
      ],
      "nodes": [
        {
          "_id": "object",
          "address1": "string",
          "address2": "string",
          "city": "string",
          "company": "string",
          "country": "string",
          "firstName": "string",
          "fullName": "string",
          "isBillingDefault": "boolean",

OrderConnection: object

Wraps a list of Orders, providing pagination cursors and information.

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

  • Relay Connection Documentation
  • Relay Connection Specification
  • Using Relay-style Connections With Apollo Client
edges:
OrderEdge

The list of nodes that match the query, wrapped in an edge to provide a cursor string for each

nodes:
Order

You can request the nodes directly to avoid the extra wrapping that NodeEdge has, if you know you will not need to paginate the results.

pageInfo:
PageInfo

Information to help a client request the next or previous page

totalCount:
Int

The total number of nodes that match your query

OrderFulfillmentGroupItemInput: object

Float

ProductConfigurationInput

Int

  },

OrderFulfillmentGroupItemsSortByField: string

Allowed values for the OrderFulfillmentGroupItems sortBy parameter

object
_id

Sort by the item ID

object
addedAt

Sort by the date and time when the item was added to the order

OrderFulfillmentStatus: string

Available order fulfillment statuses

object
completed

An order that has been completed

object
new

Newly created order that needs processing

object
processing

An order that is currently being processed

OrderInput: object

Input for placing an order

cartId:
String

The ID of the cart that is becoming an order. This is optional, and you can create an order without ever creating a cart. If you do have a cart, there are two good reasons to provide this. First, it serves as a reference. Second, it allows the Cart service to automatically delete the related cart after the order is created.

currencyCode:
String

The code for the currency in which all values are being provided

email:
String

An email address to use for order tracking and correspondence. If a logged in user is placing an order, we recommend that you use their "orders" email address, if they have one, or their default email address. Or you can ask them to provide any email address.

fulfillmentGroups:
OrderFulfillmentGroupInput

One or more fulfillment groups for the order. These are the actual orders that need to be fulfilled, separate by shop, fulfillment type, and shipping origin or destination.

shopId:
String

The shop through which the order should be placed. Payment settings from this shop will be used. Note that each fulfillment group also has a shop ID, which represents the shop that needs to fulfill that part of the order, and those shop IDs may or may not match this one.

Example
{
  "cartId": "string",
  "currencyCode": "string",
  "email": "string",
  "fulfillmentGroups": [
    {
      "data": {
        "shippingAddress": {
          "address1": "string",
          "address2": "string",
          "addressName": "string",
          "city": "string",
          "company": "string",
          "country": "string",
          "firstName": "string",
          "fullName": "string",
          "isBillingDefault": "boolean",
          "isCommercial": "boolean",

OrderItem: object

A single item in an order. The item contains information about a purchase.

_id:
ID

The order item ID

addedAt:
DateTime

" The date and time at which this item was first added to the associated cart. If an item is added, removed, and then added again, this will reflect the most recent addition. However, if an item is added twice, the quantity will increase but this date will remain the initial added date.

attributes:
OrderItemAttribute

FUTURE. Additional attributes of the chosen item. For example, if this item is for a product, socks, where blue and small options were chosen for some configurable attributes, then color:blue and size:small will be indicated here.

cancelReason:
String

If this order item is canceled, the reason for cancelation, if provided

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which the order item was created

imageURLs:
ImageSizes

The URLs for a picture of the item in various sizes

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this cart item.

optionTitle:
String

The short title of the associated option, if this is an option item

parcel:
ShippingParcel

Packing information such as item weight, height, length, and depth. Used for calculating shipping rates.

price:
Money

The price of the item at the time of purchase

productConfiguration:
ProductConfiguration

The product and chosen options

productSlug:
String

The product's slug

productTags:
TagConnection

The list of tags that have been applied to this product

productType:
String

The type of product, used to display cart items differently

productVendor:
String

The product vendor

quantity:
Int

The quantity of this item that has been added to the cart. This must be a positive integer. Remove this CartItem from it's associated cart if you want 0 of this item.

shop:
Shop

The shop associated with this cart item.

status:
String

The machine-readable order item status.

subtotal:
Money

The price of the item multiplied by the quantity of this item ordered

title:
String

A title for use in orders that conveys the selected product's title + chosen options

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this item was last updated

variantTitle:
String

The selected variant title

isTaxable:
Boolean

Is this a taxable item?

tax:
Money

Total tax calculated for this item

taxCode:
String

The tax code for this item

taxableAmount:
Money

Amount of subtotal that is taxable

taxes:
CalculatedTax

List of calculated taxes due for this item

PaymentInput: object

Input for adding order payments

amount:
Float

Amount to charge, which must be less than or equal to the order total. This is assumed to be in the same currency as the order. Set to null to charge the remaining amount to this payment method, which might be the full order total if this is the only payment.

billingAddress:
AddressInput

The billing address entered by the shopper. If omitted, the billing address on the order input will be used. Some payment methods may not require a billing address but others will fail authorization without one, so be sure that client UI code is aware of which payment methods require collecting one.

data:
JSONObject

Any additional user-provided input necessary to authorize and capture the payment

method:
PaymentMethodName

The name of the payment method to use for this payment

PaymentStatus: string

Valid payment statuses

object
adjustments

A shop operator adjusted the payment amount after the order was placed

object
approved

A shop operator has approved this payment

object
canceled

A shop operator has canceled this payment before it was captured

object
completed

A shop operator has captured this payment

object
created

Upon placing an order, the status of all payments for that order begins at 'created'

object
error

There was an error capturing the payment

object
partialRefund

A shop operator has refunded some but not all of this payment

object
refunded

A shop operator has refunded all of this payment

PlaceOrderInput: object

Input for the placeOrder mutation

clientMutationId:
String

An optional string identifying the mutation call, which will be returned in the response payload

order:
OrderInput

The order to be placed, if payment is accepted

payments:
PaymentInput

The information necessary to pay. Collect this information from the shopper during a checkout flow. You need not provide any payment input if the total is zero. The total of all payment input amount fields must add up to the order total. The first payment method where the amount field is null will be charged the remainder due.

Example
{
  "clientMutationId": "string",
  "order": {
    "cartId": "string",
    "currencyCode": "string",
    "email": "string",
    "fulfillmentGroups": [
      {
        "data": {

ProductPricingInfo: object

The product price or price range for a specific currency

compareAtPrice:
Money

A comparison price value, usually MSRP. If price is null, this will also be null. That is, only purchasable variants will have a compareAtPrice.

currency:
Currency

The code for the currency these pricing details applies to

currencyExchangePricing:
CurrencyExchangeProductPricingInfo

Pricing converted to specified currency

displayPrice:
String

UI should display this price. If a product has multiple potential prices depending on selected variants and options, then this is a price range string such as "$3.95 - $6.99". It includes the currency symbols.

maxPrice:
Float

The price of the most expensive possible variant+option combination

minPrice:
Float

The price of the least expensive possible variant+option combination

price:
Float

For variants with no options and for options, this will always be set to a price. For variants with options and products, this will be null. There must be a price for a variant to be added to a cart or purchased. Otherwise you would instead add one of its child options to a cart.

    "decimal": "string",
    "format": "string",
    "rate": "number",
    "scale": "number",
    "symbol": "string",
    "thousand": "string"
  },
  "currencyExchangePricing": {
    "compareAtPrice": {
      "amount": "number",
      "currency": {
        "_id": "object",
        "code": "string",
        "decimal": "string",
        "format": "string",
        "rate": "number",
        "scale": "number",
        "symbol": "string",
        "thousand": "string"
      },
      "displayAmount": "string"
    },
    "currency": {
      "_id": "object",
      "code": "string",
      "decimal": "string",
      "format": "string",
      "rate": "number",
      "scale": "number",
      "symbol": "string",
      "thousand": "string"

RoleConnection: object

Wraps a list of Roles, providing pagination cursors and information.

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

  • Relay Connection Documentation
  • Relay Connection Specification
  • Using Relay-style Connections With Apollo Client
edges:
RoleEdge

The list of nodes that match the query, wrapped in an edge to provide a cursor string for each

nodes:
Role

You can request the nodes directly to avoid the extra wrapping that NodeEdge has, if you know you will not need to paginate the results.

pageInfo:
PageInfo

Information to help a client request the next or previous page

totalCount:
Int

The total number of nodes that match your query

Example
{
  "edges": [
    {
      "cursor": "object",

      }
    }

  ],

      "errors": "string",

        {
          "channel": "string",
          "channelId": "number",
          "channel_market": "string",
          "country": "string",
          "errors": "string",
          "extraInfo": [
            {
              "description": "string",
              "example": "string",
              "from": "string",
              "order": "number",
              "status": "string",
              "to": "string"
            }

ShopSettings: object

App settings for a specific shop. Plugins extend the ShopSettings type to support whatever settings they need.

doNotUse:
String

A fake setting necessary until some plugin extends this with a real setting

canSellVariantWithoutInventory:
Boolean

If there is no known inventory for a product configuration, this setting determines whether that product configuration can be sold and should appear to be available.

isShippingRatesFulfillmentEnabled:
Boolean

If false no defined shipping rates will be used when fulfillment quotes are requested for a cart or order. A quick way to disable the entire reaction-shipping-rates plugin temporarily.

defaultTaxCode:
String

The default value to use for taxCode property of a product

fallbackTaxServiceName:
String

The name of the tax service to fall back to if the primary tax service is down. This will match the name field of one of the services returned by the taxServices query.

primaryTaxServiceName:
String

The name of the tax service to use for calculating taxes on carts and orders. This will match the name field of one of the services returned by the taxServices query.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeAdminOnly:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be visible only to admins by default.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBePubliclyVisible:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be public API/Storefront visible by default.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeSecondaryNavOnly:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be a secondary navigation item by default.

sitemapRefreshPeriod:
String

This setting controls how often the sitemaps for the shop will be rebuilt

Example
{
  "doNotUse": "string",
  "canSellVariantWithoutInventory": "boolean",
  "isShippingRatesFulfillmentEnabled": "boolean",
  "defaultTaxCode": "string",
  "fallbackTaxServiceName": "string",
  "primaryTaxServiceName": "string",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeAdminOnly": "boolean",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBePubliclyVisible": "boolean",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeSecondaryNavOnly": "boolean",
  "sitemapRefreshPeriod": "string"
}

ShopSettingsUpdates: object

Updates for app settings that are not shop specific. Plugins extend this input type to support whatever settings they need. All fields must be optional.

doNotUse:
String

Do not use this field

canSellVariantWithoutInventory:
Boolean

If there is no known inventory for a product configuration, this setting determines whether that product configuration can be sold and should appear to be available.

isShippingRatesFulfillmentEnabled:
Boolean

Set to false to prevent any defined shipping rates from being used when fulfillment quotes are requested for a cart or order. A quick way to disable the entire reaction-shipping-rates plugin temporarily.

defaultTaxCode:
String

The default value to use for taxCode property of a product

fallbackTaxServiceName:
String

Optionally, set the name of the tax service to fall back to if the primary tax service is down. This must match the name field of one of the services returned by the taxServices query.

primaryTaxServiceName:
String

Set the name of the tax service to use for calculating taxes on carts and orders. This will match the name field of one of the services returned by the taxServices query. There will be no taxes charged for any carts or orders if this is not set.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeAdminOnly:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be visible only to admins by default.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBePubliclyVisible:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be public API/Storefront visible by default.

shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeSecondaryNavOnly:
Boolean

Whether a navigation item added to the navigation tree should be a secondary navigation item by default.

sitemapRefreshPeriod:
String

This setting controls how often the sitemaps for the shop will be rebuilt

Example
{
  "doNotUse": "string",
  "canSellVariantWithoutInventory": "boolean",
  "isShippingRatesFulfillmentEnabled": "boolean",
  "defaultTaxCode": "string",
  "fallbackTaxServiceName": "string",
  "primaryTaxServiceName": "string",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeAdminOnly": "boolean",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBePubliclyVisible": "boolean",
  "shouldNavigationTreeItemsBeSecondaryNavOnly": "boolean",
  "sitemapRefreshPeriod": "string"
}

Whether to allow ordering this product configuration when there is insufficient quantity available

inventoryInStock:
Int

Current quantity of this product configuration in stock

inventoryReserved:
Int

Current quantity of this product configuration unavailable for ordering. This value is calculated by the system based on this product variant being in not-yet-approved orders.

isEnabled:
Boolean

Whether the SimpleInventory plugin should manage inventory for this product configuration

lowInventoryWarningThreshold:
Int

The "low quantity" flag will be applied to this product configuration when the available quantity is at or below this threshold

productConfiguration:
ProductConfiguration

The product and chosen options this info applies to

Example

Tag: object

Represents a single tag

_id:
ID

The tag ID

createdAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this tag was created

displayTitle:
String

A string of the title to be displayed on a Tag Listing Page

featuredProductIds:
ID

A list of the IDs of top products in this tag

heroMediaUrl:
String

A string containing the hero image url for a Tag Listing Page

isDeleted:
Boolean

If true, this object should be considered deleted. Soft deleted objects are not returned in query results unless you explicitly ask for them.

isTopLevel:
Boolean

If true, this tag should be shown at the top level of the tag hierarchy

isVisible:
Boolean

If true, this tag's Tag Listing Page should be visible to the public

metafields:
Metafield

Arbitrary additional metadata about this tag

name:
String

The display name for the tag. This is unique within a given shop.

position:
Int

The tag's position relative to other tags at the same level of the tag hierarchy

shop:
Shop

The shop to which this tag belongs

slug:
String

A unique URL-safe string representing this tag for links

subTagIds:
ID

A list of the IDs of tags that have this tag as their parent in the tag hierarchy, in the user-defined order

updatedAt:
DateTime

The date and time at which this tag was last updated

subTags:
TagConnection

A paged list of tags that have this tag as their parent in the tag hierarchy. Currently only three levels are supported.

TaxSource

UpdateSimpleInventoryInput: object

Input for the updateSimpleInventory mutation. In addition to shopId, at least one field to update is required.

canBackorder:
Boolean

Whether to allow ordering this product configuration when there is insufficient quantity available. Set this to true or false if you want to update it.

clientMutationId:
String

An optional string identifying the mutation call, which will be returned in the response payload

inventoryInStock:
Int

Current quantity of this product configuration in stock. Set this to an integer if you want to update it.

isEnabled:
Boolean

Whether the SimpleInventory plugin should manage inventory for this product configuration. Set this to true or false if you want to update it.

lowInventoryWarningThreshold:
Int

The "low quantity" flag will be applied to this product configuration when the available quantity is at or below this threshold. Set this to an integer if you want to update it.

productConfiguration:
ProductConfigurationInput

The product and chosen options this info applies to

shopId:
ID

Shop that owns the product

Example

  "isEnabled": "boolean",
  "lowInventoryWarningThreshold": "number",
  "productConfiguration": {
    "productId": "object",
    "productVariantId": "object"

UpdateTaxRateInput: object

The input for updating a tax rate. Note that missing values will cause the field to be cleared, so send all optional fields with every request unless they aren't currently set or you intend to clear them.

clientMutationId:
String

An optional string identifying the mutation call, which will be returned in the response payload

country:
String

An optional country code to limit where this tax is applied based on destination address

postal:
String

An optional postal code to limit where this tax is applied based on destination address

rate:
Float

The tax rate. For example, 0.05 for a 5% sales tax.

region:
String

An optional region (e.g., state) to limit where this tax is applied based on destination address

shopId:
ID

Shop ID

sourcing:
TaxSource

Whether the country, postal, and region filters apply to the origin address or the destination address

taxCode:
String

An optional tax code, to apply this tax rate to only products that have this tax code

taxRateId:
ID

ID of the tax rate you want to update

Example
{
  "clientMutationId": "string",
  "country": "string",
  "postal": "string",
  "rate": "number",
  "region": "string",
  "shopId": "object",
  "sourcing": "string",
  "taxCode": "string",
  "taxRateId": "object"
}

VendorConnection: object

Wraps an array of vendors, providing pagination cursors and information.

For information about what Relay-compatible connections are and how to use them, see the following articles:

  • Relay Connection Documentation
  • Relay Connection Specification
  • Using Relay-style Connections With Apollo Client
edges:
VendorEdge

The list of nodes that match the query, wrapped in an edge to provide a cursor string for each

nodes:
Vendor

You can request the nodes directly to avoid the extra wrapping that NodeEdge has, if you know you will not need to paginate the results.

pageInfo:
PageInfo

Information to help a client request the next or previous page

totalCount:
Int

The total number of nodes that match your query
